The Chronicle Prosper Ndlovu in Lilongwe, Malawi LIKE Zimbabwe, Malawi is driving at increasing its agricultural output and in so doing, it is keen to mechanise its small holder farmers as well as securing synergies with regional member states.  Zimbabwean companies that are exhibiting here at the Malawi-Zimbabwe Trade Exhibition, which ends today, are receiving huge interest related to the supply of agro-related products and expertise.  Farm implements maker, Zimplow, irrigation specialists, Maka Resources and agro-processing industries are some of the businesses that received high interest. 